You lead the Horde. Your goal is to defeat all enemies and survive. Every player is on their own! A player is defeated when they have no units left.

The Horde consists of five types of units with varying strengths. Destroy the villages. From the village houses, soul shards drop. By taking a soul shard of its level, a unit upgrades to the next level.

By killing enemies, you obtain their soul shards, which might be more beneficial than raiding villages. During the breaks between battles, the Horde's numbers quickly replenish.

Regardless of where you are, the safe space for maneuvering gradually decreases. Keep an eye on the circle on the map.
